abstract: LOS ANGELES, March 9 (AP)  JoAnne Carner shot a five-under-par 67 in the final round to win the $125,000 Ladies' Professional Golf Association tournament today at Rancho Park by three shots.

LOS ANGELES, March 8 (AP)-- Kathy Postlewait, seeking her first Ladies' Professional Golf Association victory, fired a tour-under-par 68 today to take the second-round lead in a $125,000 tournament at Rancho Park.

abstract: Mayor Koch flew to Washington for a private, 90-minute luncheon with President and Mrs. Carter at the White House yesterday and engaged in a wide-ranging discussion that covered politics, New York City's fiscal problems, the Mayor's recent trip to China and the United States vote against Israel in the United Nations.
headline_main: KOCH HAS LUNCHEON WITH THE PRESIDENT; Carter Is 'Supportive' About Fiscal Condition of City, Mayor Says After Private Conference Support for Carter Reiterated City Counting on Federal Aid

abstract: You've come a long way baby, from Arkansas to Hollywood," sings Loretta Lynn. All of a sudden, country-andWestern music, the fastest  growing genre of popular music, has been discovered by Hollywood. After decades of being confined to lowbudget action films for the drive-in circuit, country music and country-music themes are showing up in big-studio, nationally distributed films.
headline_main: 'Country' Movies Are in Tune With the 'New Patriotism'; 'Country' Movies Are In Tune With 'New Patriotism'

abstract: The scene is a sprawling ranch in Texas, where a tall, handsome man in a cowboy hat and well-worn Levi jacket is walk  ing arm in arm with a striking woman, his wife as it turns out. Could this be Rock Hudson and Elizabeth Taylor in "Giant"? No, it's John and Nellie Connally in a made-for-television political commercial.
headline_main: The Art Of Selling Politicians Like Soap On TV; Selling Politicians Like Soap on TV
